item.title: Rachel add a quote by Hubert Selby Jr.
item.description: "They held each other and kissed and pushed each others' darkness into the corner, believing in each others' light, each others' dream." -- Hubert Selby Jr.

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Chuck Palahniuk
item.description: "There's an opposite to déjà vu. They call it jamais vu. It's when you meet the same people or visit places, again and again, but each time is the first. Everybody is always a stranger. Nothing is ever familiar." -- Chuck Palahniuk

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Friedrich Nietzsche
item.description: "Invisible threads are the strongest ties." -- Friedrich Nietzsche

item.title: Rachel add a quote by John Muir
item.description: "Thousands of tired, nerve-shaken, over-civilized people are beginning to find out going to the mountains is going home; that wilderness is a necessity..." -- John Muir

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Goethe
item.description: "The world is so empty if one thinks only of mountains, rivers & cities; but to know someone who thinks & feels with us, & who, though distant, is close to us in spirit, this makes the earth for us an inhabited garden." -- Goethe

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Albert Schweitzer
item.description: "Just as the wave cannot exist for itself, but is ever a part of the heaving surface of the ocean, so must I never live my life for itself, but always in the experience which is going on around me." -- Albert Schweitzer

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "You know you're in love when you can't fall asleep because reality is finally better than your dreams." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Stephen Chbosky
item.description: "We accept the love we think we deserve." -- Stephen Chbosky

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Martin Luther King Jr.
item.description: "Darkness cannot drive out darkness: only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out hate: only love can do that." -- Martin Luther King Jr.

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Andre Gide
item.description: "It is better to be hated for what you are than to be loved for what you are not." -- Andre Gide

item.title: Rachel add a quote by Lao Tzu
item.description: "Being deeply loved by someone gives you strength, while loving someone deeply gives you courage." -- Lao Tzu

item.title: Rachel add a quote by H.G. Wells
item.description: "Every time I see an adult on a bicycle, I no longer despair for the future of the human race." -- H.G. Wells
